MergeTreeNode

MergeTreeNode(org.w3c.dom.Element eMElt,
              int treeMergeType,
              int treeDomSide,
              boolean checkAccumConstraints,
              MergeTree mergeTree)
        throws MTException
Constructor - creates the a MergeTreeNode corresponding to mergeTemplateElement and recursively calls itself to create MergeTreeNodes for all of the children of mergeTemplateElement.

Parameters:
eMElt - ElementMerge element which contains the merge specification to be translated to this MergeTreeNode
treeMergeType - The MergeType (inner, outer, etc) specified at the tree level (default for the whole tree)
treeDomSide - The Dominant Side (left/right) specified at the tree level (default for the whole tree)
checkAccumConstraints - true/false depending on whether we should verify that this MergeTemplate is valid for use in accumulator. Accumulate has certain restrictions beyond those for a general merge template, if checkAccumConstraints is true and these constraints are violated
Throws:
MTException

createLocalKeyValues

public void createLocalKeyValues(org.w3c.dom.Element elt,
                                 java.lang.String tagName,
                                 ArrayStack localKeyValList)
                          throws ShutdownException
Creates a local key value for an element. Will search the element for key values as described by local key spec and will concatenate those to create a local key value string. Allows multiple matches to the local key spec (local key must contain only one path in that case) in this element and returns a stack/array of strings with those values

Parameters:
elt - The element whose local key should be created
tagName - The tag name to annotate the local key value with, due to support for renaming, this sometimes is not the same as the tag name of the element uugh, this is UGLY - I don't like it
